  "text": "Intracranial self-stimulation. As we have previously shown [CITATION_1] , alcohol (0.6, 1.7, and 2.4 g/kg, p.o.) had biphasic, dose-dependent effects on BSR threshold (y 0 ) in C57BL/6J mice ( Figure 2d ). These effects depended on LEV or saline pretreatment (F 3,27 ¼ 3.2, po0.05). Post hoc analyses revealed that 0.6 g/kg alcohol (p.o.) significantly lowered y 0 when mice were pretreated with saline, but not with LEV 100.0 mg/kg (i.p.). The 1.7 g/kg alcohol dose (p.o.) significantly elevated y 0 when mice were pretreated with LEV, but not with saline. The 2.4 g/kg alcohol dose significantly elevated y 0 when mice were pretreated with either saline or LEV. Pretreatment with LEV 100.0 mg/kg appeared to increase maximum response rate, but there was no interaction between LEV and alcohol dose (F 3,27 ¼ 0.18, p ¼ 0.91; Figure 2d ).",
